key_points: A second body camera video reveals Gabby Petito admitted to hitting Brian Laundrie before he hit her during a police stop on Aug. 12, 2021.
Petito and Laundrie were pulled over near Arches National Park after a 911 caller reported seeing them fight.
Petito was reported missing on Sept. 11, and her body was found on Sept. 19 near Grand Teton National Park in Wyoming, ruling her death a homicide.
Laundrie, named a person of interest in Petito's disappearance, disappeared after returning to Florida without Petito on Sept. 1.
Federal investigators have issued an arrest warrant for Laundrie over unauthorized use of a debit card.
In the video, Petito describes Laundrie becoming frustrated and locking her out of the van, while Laundrie mentions trying to push her away during a confrontation.
Moab police officers discussed but ultimately decided against charging Petito with assault, considering her not a threat to Laundrie.
An officer expressed sympathy towards Petito, suggesting she was also a victim of her own emotional and psychological struggles.
The city of Moab announced an investigation into the police department's handling of the case, and Moab Police Chief Bret Edge went on leave under the Family and Medical Leave Act.
As of Friday afternoon, the search for Laundrie continues.
